*must* aim for the largest possible result.  A single blockbuster best
seller can be so successful, it can pay for years of failures.

The board wargames we played 30 and 40 years ago could never have
competed with the best selling games of that era and no one ever
expected them to; likewise today's PC wargames.  That's why most of
the games we talk about around here are the products of hobbyists and
independent (read: impoverished) developers.

